# Worktrees

## Overview

Manage git worktrees using [gtr (git-worktree-runner)](https://github.com/coderabbitai/git-worktree-runner) for isolated development.

**Announce at start:** "I'm using the worktrees skill to manage git worktrees."

## Prerequisites

```bash
git gtr --version || echo "Run setup-gtr skill first"
```

## Quick Reference

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Create worktree | `git gtr new <branch>` |
| Create from current branch | `git gtr new <branch> --from-current` |
| Create + open editor | `git gtr new <branch> -e` |
| Create + launch Claude | `git gtr new <branch> -a` |
| Run command in worktree | `git gtr run <branch> <cmd>` |
| Rename worktree + branch | `git gtr mv <old> <new>` |
| Copy files to worktree | `git gtr copy <branch>` |
| Health check | `git gtr doctor` |
| List worktrees | `git gtr list` |
| Remove worktree | `git gtr rm <branch>` |
| Cleanup merged | `git gtr clean --merged` |

## Common Workflow

### 1. Create Feature Worktree

From main (default behavior):

```bash
git gtr new feature/my-feature
```

From current branch (to include your latest changes):

```bash
git gtr new feature/my-feature --from-current
```

This:
- Creates `~/worktrees/<repo>/feature-my-feature/`
- Copies .env and config files
- Runs `just install`

**Important:** Without `--from-current`, gtr branches from main by default. Use `--from-current` when you need changes from your current branch.

### 2. Do Work

```bash
cd ~/worktrees/my-repo/feature-my-feature
# implement, commit, push
```

### 3. Create PR and Merge

```bash
gh pr create
# review, merge
```

### 4. Cleanup

```bash
git gtr rm feature/my-feature --delete-branch
```

Or cleanup all merged at once:

```bash
git gtr clean --merged
```

## Directory Convention

All worktrees use `~/worktrees/<repo-name>/`:

```
~/worktrees/
└── my-repo/
    ├── feature-auth/
    ├── fix-bug-123/
    └── experiment-new-api/
```

## Configuration

Repository `.gtrconfig` (gitconfig syntax, use relative paths for portability):

```ini
[worktrees]
    dir = ../worktrees

[copy]
    include = .env
    include = .env.local
    include = *.local.md
    include = .claude/*.local.md

[hook]
    postCreate = just install

[editor]
    default = code

[ai]
    default = claude
```

**Note:** Each `include` is a separate line (multi-value), not comma-separated.

## Error Handling

| Error | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| "worktree already exists" | Use existing or `git gtr rm` first |
| "branch not found" | `git fetch origin <branch>` |
| "uncommitted changes" | Commit/stash or use `--force` |

